    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-01-15T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-01-15T21:00:00-05:00" n="898"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d898">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102 Kulangsu/283: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Amoy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVitty</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Amoy</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-01-16T10:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 16, 1940—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 17—2:48 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to my telegrams of January 9, 9 a.m. and January 11, 3 p.m.<note n="71"
                        xml:id="d898fn71">Neither printed.</note> Ng Lian Hong, the victim of the
                    attempted assassination on January 8, died yesterday morning, and yesterday
                    morning the Japanese Consul General<note n="72" xml:id="d898fn72">G.
                        Uchida.</note> presented the Municipal Council with a demand for the
                    immediate appointment of 10 additional Formosan police. The restrictions on
                    traffic between Kulangsu and the mainland are being strictly enforced by the
                    Japanese Navy and firewood supplies are again becoming low.</p>
                <p>In connection with the assassination of Ng, it is believed interesting to note
                    that although he was connected with the Amoy puppet government he resided in the
                    International Settlement and not in Amoy.</p>
                <p>Sent to Peiping. Repeated to Chungking, Shanghai. Peiping please repeat to
                    Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVitty</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
